Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.57,0:00:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Corinna.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.74,0:00:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Why was your letter so short?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.49,0:00:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like Eupolis who practiced, practiced,\Nand practiced astrology,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:18.46,0:00:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,my heart is troubled by you.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.05,0:00:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Idas's gold faded, and Galonus the carpenter...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.62,0:00:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.51,0:00:33.62,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no need for you to read any further.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.14,0:00:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.31,0:00:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.10,0:00:39.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.19,0:00:44.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry. Did I do anything to upset you?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.65,0:00:50.81,Default,,0,0,0,,People who can't pronounce Latin correctly\Nhave no right to read a book to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.70,0:00:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.99,0:00:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll try harder in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.62,0:00:56.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm telling you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.75,0:02:38.93,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(700,700)\pos(360,340)}Thursday's Boy
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.01,0:02:44.89,Names,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\an8\}Munich University\NFriedrich Emmanuel School
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.88,0:02:51.49,Default,,0,0,0,,You really got scolded\Nharshly at the mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.22,0:02:54.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Cheer up.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.81,0:02:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Business management major, Karl Neuman.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.73,0:03:02.11,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you know about me?\NWhat's your name?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.48,0:03:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Lotte Frank,\Na cultural anthropology major.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.73,0:03:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you also reading\Nbooks to him as a part-time job?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.07,0:03:12.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, I just take care of the place.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.70,0:03:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Only male students read to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.62,0:03:19.06,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the person who\Nreads to him on Tuesdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.41,0:03:24.86,Default,,0,0,0,,On other days, he has other students come and\Nread to him since his eyesight has worsened.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:25.59,0:03:27.78,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think of him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.34,0:03:32.16,Default,,0,0,0,,That mysterious millionaire,\NHans George Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.59,0:03:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,I... I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.47,0:03:38.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I just thought that the wage he was paying for the\Npart-time job was pretty good, so I jumped at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.10,0:03:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you heard the numerous\Nrumors about him?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.35,0:03:48.13,Default,,0,0,0,,They say there's a phone line in the mansion where he can\Nmanipulate the German stock market any way he wishes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.90,0:03:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They call him the Howard Hughes of Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.78,0:03:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,He has no family and no acquaintances, but his\Nfortune just keeps growing and growing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.58,0:04:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you think he\Ndoes with all that money?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.12,0:04:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.16,0:04:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There's an even bigger mystery than that!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.79,0:04:07.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He is also called the Vampire of Bayern.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.13,0:04:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Vampire?!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.88,0:04:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,When the clock strikes two in the morning, he gets\Nin a car that looks like a Hearse and goes to town.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.56,0:04:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks just like a scene\Nfrom a gothic horror movie.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.02,0:04:23.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He was probably just going out for a stroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.85,0:04:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to confirm for myself whether\Nor not it was just an ordinary stroll.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.15,0:04:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Confirm for yourself? What are you saying?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.48,0:04:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It's for my research paper.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.61,0:04:37.06,Default,,0,0,0,,"Mental Activity of Medieval and Current\NDay Financial Figures in Bayern."
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.91,0:04:39.87,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a great sample for sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.24,0:04:42.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So you investigated me in the same manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.83,0:04:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I only looked up your name and major.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.38,0:04:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,You shouldn't worry about his yelling at you.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.13,0:04:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He says cruel things to all the students.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.51,0:04:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm used to getting yelled at and beaten up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.05,0:04:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Used to...?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.97,0:05:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A lot happened with my foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.10,0:05:08.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You aren't from one of the\Nlocal high schools, are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.11,0:05:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So you {\i1}did {\i0} investigate me.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.69,0:05:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. You don't have any parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.78,0:05:21.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is I was hoping to meet my real\Nmother in Munich, so I transferred here.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.08,0:05:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So your mother is in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.37,0:05:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you seen her?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.79,0:05:29.19,Default,,0,0,0,,No. I don't care anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.46,0:05:31.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.34,0:05:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,You're finally close to her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.92,0:05:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,You probably know her name, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.22,0:05:36.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.26,0:05:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.47,0:05:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, it doesn't matter anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.47,0:05:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.06,0:05:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm interested now.\NI'll figure it out eventually anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.27,0:05:47.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.73,0:05:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.61,0:05:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,If you know that much,\Nit shouldn't be hard to find her.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.44,0:05:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Go see her. She'll be happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.45,0:05:59.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you, it doesn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.25,0:06:06.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Margot Langer... Margot Langer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.25,0:06:11.07,Default,,0,0,0,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.96,0:06:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The galloping of the chestnut-colored horse was like\Nlightning striking the ground and large waves crashing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.80,0:06:22.33,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't take it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:22.93,0:06:25.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I only love beautiful things.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.02,0:06:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't listen to that anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.44,0:06:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell me?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.20,0:06:40.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I looked up your mother.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.12,0:06:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,What can I say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.74,0:06:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay. Just drop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.87,0:06:50.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, isn't there anything\NI can do to help you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.17,0:06:53.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks, but don't worry about me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.92,0:06:54.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.55,0:07:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte, you said that you wanted to see\Nwhat Hans Schuwald does at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.77,0:07:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Can I come with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.31,0:07:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course. If you come with me,\NI'll feel a lot better.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.40,0:07:18.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's true!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.99,0:07:22.37,Default,,0,0,0,,This is my first big scoop.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.99,0:07:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.66,0:07:33.15,Default,,0,0,0,,It's perfectly clear that one of the men who founded\Nthis school in 1502, Bishop Gropius, wrote this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.83,0:07:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The most important part is this line here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.30,0:07:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,"In the second-to-last larger year,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.88,0:07:41.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Thursday Boy will come to this land,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.91,0:07:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,and the books shall be engulfed in flames,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.97,0:07:46.87,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole world will\Nbe wrapped in sorrow."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.64,0:07:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So what does that mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.06,0:07:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Will you ever get it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.69,0:07:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,This... "In the second-to-last larger year"...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.82,0:07:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's 1996! So it's this year.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.24,0:08:00.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.82,0:08:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The "larger year" means leap years.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.91,0:08:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The only leap years left in this\Ncentury are this year and 2000.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.66,0:08:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,"The Thursday Boy will come to this land,\Nand the books shall be engulfed in flame."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.08,0:08:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,"The books of this land in flames"\Nmeans that this school will burn.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.46,0:08:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Then who is this "Thursday Boy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.84,0:08:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Thursday is "Donnerstag."\NThe origin of that is "Donner."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.05,0:08:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, "thunder."\NIt must be the lightning god!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.10,0:08:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What a whopper!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.14,0:08:32.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is no time to be laughing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.94,0:08:34.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This will be the hit story of the next issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.02,0:08:39.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We won't have a problem writing this,\Nbut who's going to believe it?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.32,0:08:42.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd believe that a god of destruction\Nwould come to this school?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.17,0:08:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Screw the "Vampire of Bayern"!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.58,0:08:59.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this the truth behind\Nthe mysterious night out?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.84,0:09:02.13,Default,,0,0,0,,What a let down!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.13,0:09:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Shh! Here he comes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.81,0:09:10.79,Default,,0,0,0,,How ridiculous.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.31,0:09:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.39,0:09:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Take care.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.94,0:09:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.69,0:09:16.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to go take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.56,0:09:17.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Go where?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.95,0:09:29.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's give up already.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.12,0:09:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This isn't the place for a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.20,0:09:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.00,0:09:38.11,Default,,0,0,0,,"I only love beautiful things."
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.17,0:09:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.13,0:09:45.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to know how low a man he really is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.64,0:09:51.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It's open.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.06,0:10:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're looking for a girl,\Nthis is the wrong place.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:02.82,0:10:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I retired a long time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.40,0:10:07.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.70,0:10:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You should introduce yourself first\Nbefore you ask someone's name.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.92,0:10:19.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.05,0:10:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like college students.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.34,0:10:30.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. We work part time for Mr. Hans Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.97,0:10:32.87,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you want with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.51,0:10:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does Hans Schuwald come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.56,0:10:41.55,Default,,0,0,0,,"He comes for pleasure."
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I'd like to say, but it seems that his\Nthing down there doesn't work anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.20,0:10:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,He comes to give me money.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.41,0:10:54.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.45,0:11:01.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally. When I came to him and told him\Nwho I was, he cried and apologized to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.04,0:11:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,He left me with a child and threw\Nme away like trash.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.67,0:11:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, don't tell me... that you're\NHans Schuwald's child?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.35,0:11:12.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.93,0:11:13.62,Default,,0,0,0,,You're lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.22,0:11:17.88,Default,,0,0,0,,You're not Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.31,0:11:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right. It was in the paper\Na year ago. "Former..."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.61,0:11:28.76,Default,,0,0,0,,"Former Prostitute Margot Langer\NMurdered -- Killer Unknown."
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.49,0:11:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,His mother is already dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.78,0:11:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You're using the name of Margot Langer\Nto swindle Hans Schuwald out of money.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.75,0:11:46.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows it, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.46,0:11:51.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He gives me money, even though he knows\NI'm not the real Margot Langer.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.01,0:11:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,He knows that giving all his money away\Nwon't bring the real Margot Langer back.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.35,0:12:00.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's his way of paying for his sins.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.25,0:12:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,With money! Money! Money!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.69,0:12:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,A man who has lived only for money can't\Nthink of anything other than money.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.15,0:12:14.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It might sound a bit arrogant, but\Npeople aren't all that different.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.62,0:12:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a method where introducing yourself\Nas his son gets you a piece of that dying\Nman's ridiculously large fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.22,0:12:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.75,0:12:27.86,Default,,0,0,0,,I might be a liar, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.01,0:12:32.49,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm talking about.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.47,0:12:36.20,Default,,0,0,0,,There's another one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.72,0:12:39.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Another boy who calls himself his son.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.02,0:12:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He came here with the same story.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.48,0:12:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.36,0:12:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.15,0:12:53.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be. He's lying.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.24,0:12:58.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know who's telling a lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.37,0:13:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You both look like imposters to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.54,0:13:04.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.06,0:13:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He's the same as you.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.83,0:13:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You take turns reading to him\Non different days, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:11.63,0:13:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,That boy is also one of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.09,0:13:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,He is the "Thursday Boy."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.09,0:13:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you tell her that\Nyou were the real one?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.85,0:13:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been sent to live with\Nmany foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.48,0:13:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,There were good ones and bad ones,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.85,0:13:39.55,Default,,0,0,0,,but the ones I have now\Nreally take care of me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.48,0:13:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel that I could never thank them enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.28,0:13:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But I've always felt that I\Nneeded to meet my real parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.82,0:13:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I wanted to know how low\Nmy real father was...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.95,0:13:55.03,Default,,0,0,0,,so that I could love my\Ncurrent parents with all my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.83,0:13:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.80,0:14:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Have you ever seen the "Thursday Boy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.76,0:14:09.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I have Thursdays off, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.26,0:14:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Once I went to get something\NI had left behind, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.39,0:14:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see him?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.19,0:14:17.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.31,0:14:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He was blonde and had a handsome face...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.63,0:14:31.68,Names,,0,0,0,,{\fad(700,700)\pos(360,280)}Monday
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.12,0:14:32.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.62,0:14:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Who is the "Thursday Boy"?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.37,0:14:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,There's a boy here pretending to be me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.05,0:14:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Got it? Listen to what Momma\Nhas to say to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.51,0:14:49.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this money and get on the fifth train line.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.55,0:14:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Get off at the eighth station. A lady\Nnamed Marta will be there.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.10,0:14:55.21,Default,,0,0,0,,What about you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.68,0:14:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I told you that I can't go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.31,0:15:01.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Are the police chasing you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.23,0:15:04.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to be with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.65,0:15:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay with me, you'll be put\Ninto an orphanage.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.40,0:15:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you stay here, people will call\Nyou the son of a whore.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.28,0:15:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.91,0:15:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My father is Hans George Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.13,0:15:23.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Who did you hear that from?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.71,0:15:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Mrs. Bella from across the street said so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.38,0:15:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,He's rich, isn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:28.80,0:15:32.29,Default,,0,0,0,,She said that I was abandoned by my father.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.48,0:15:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You weren't abandoned.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.94,0:15:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I'll go see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.86,0:15:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.98,0:15:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Then when?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.65,0:15:47.89,Default,,0,0,0,,When you grow up.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.95,0:15:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to see him, see him then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.41,0:15:54.18,Default,,0,0,0,,But you mustn't want anything from him.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.70,0:15:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You must not hate him if\Nhe treats you coldly.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.33,0:15:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.75,0:16:05.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I don't hate him.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.05,0:16:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Take this.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.18,0:16:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father gave you this\Nwhen you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.52,0:16:25.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.19,0:16:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured it out!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.90,0:16:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured out who the "Thursday Boy" is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.28,0:16:34.35,Default,,0,0,0,,His name is Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.70,0:16:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He's a philosophical literature major.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.70,0:16:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He reads books to Mr. Schuwald\Nas a part-time job on Thursdays.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.46,0:16:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.21,0:16:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.63,0:16:49.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The lecture just ended for this classroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.47,0:16:54.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.05,0:16:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd like to see Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.81,0:17:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Is Edmund here?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.94,0:17:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Edmund? He didn't come today.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.56,0:17:06.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what they say.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.69,0:17:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Really...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.15,0:17:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.24,0:17:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But it's only a matter of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.24,0:17:19.89,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll catch that imposter.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:20.41,0:17:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You're the one who should\Ninherit Schuwald's fortune.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.25,0:17:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not true.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.75,0:17:26.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.04,0:17:29.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care about the inheritance.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.46,0:17:30.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.51,0:17:33.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't care how much money\Nhe cons out of him.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.59,0:17:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.68,0:17:36.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You just...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.97,0:17:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't forgive Edmund Fahren for\Ncalling himself my mother's son.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.75,0:17:55.51,Names,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(360,280)}Tuesday
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.90,0:17:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The petals of your silk flower\Npetals flutter in the wind,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.82,0:17:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and a mocking bird sang in my heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.96,0:18:10.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You haven't said anything today,\NMr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.30,0:18:16.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Why didn't you quit after I\Nyelled at you so much?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.34,0:18:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Was the money that good?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.68,0:18:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not it...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.48,0:18:27.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.19,0:18:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you talk about anything but money?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.11,0:18:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Just as you said.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.99,0:18:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are your parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.37,0:18:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I have foster parents.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.58,0:18:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.95,0:18:50.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Forgive me for asking, but do you\Nwant to meet your real parents?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.09,0:18:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The truth is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.38,0:19:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems the boy who appeared\Nthis time is the real thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.43,0:19:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,He doesn't want money.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.77,0:19:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,He?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.77,0:19:09.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. I was talking to myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.15,0:19:12.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You can go home.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.53,0:19:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I forgot to mention...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.83,0:19:25.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Your Latin's gotten better.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.83,0:19:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:36.57,0:19:39.40,Names,,0,0,0,,{\fad(500,0)\pos(360,280)}Wednesday
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.88,0:19:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems like Edmund Fahren\Nis absent again today.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.64,0:19:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,He must have caught a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.43,0:19:49.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Either way, tomorrow is Thursday.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.19,0:19:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He'll show up for his job\Nwith Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.40,0:19:57.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. He'll show his true\Ncolors in front of Mr. Schuwald.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.03,0:20:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll get him... We'll get him good!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.30,0:20:04.80,Names,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,500)\pos(360,280)}Thursday
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.58,0:20:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,He hasn't shown up. It's been an hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.37,0:20:13.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If he caught a cold,\Nhe might be staying home.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.92,0:20:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, do you want to give\Nhim a surprise visit?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.01,0:20:21.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You went so far as to look\Nup his address already?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.39,0:20:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,204, 204, 204.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.85,0:20:31.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.07,0:20:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, go on.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.87,0:21:13.37,Names,,0,0,0,,{\pos(360,280)}Friday
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.69,0:21:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,How horrible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.94,0:21:20.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone's talking about Edmund Fahren.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.65,0:21:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't believe he committed suicide.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.99,0:21:27.10,Default,,0,0,0,,His last testament is in the\Nschool paper, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:28.41,0:21:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,"I can't pretend any longer."
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.83,0:21:33.11,Default,,0,0,0,,He's talking about...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.92,0:21:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, after pretending to be Schuwald's son and becoming\Nclose to him, he was consumed by pangs of guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:41.26,0:21:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,If he was going to be troubled so much that he would\Nkill himself, he shouldn't have done it in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.60,0:21:52.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Lotte.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.73,0:21:54.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Yesterday was quite a ruckus, wasn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.23,0:22:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, it was. We were questioned\Nby the police all day.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.69,0:22:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,My reading was called off today.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.03,0:22:06.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Mr. Schuwald was very troubled by the news.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.07,0:22:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Karl, I'll introduce you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.20,0:22:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the Friday reader.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.33,0:22:12.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Nice to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.79,0:22:16.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Hi. I'm Karl Neuman,\Na business management major.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.50,0:22:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm a law major, Johan Liebert.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.15,0:23:53.59,Title,,0,0,0,,{\fad(1000,0)\pos(360,340)}The Secret Woods
